# PBIR Visual JSON Standards

## File Location

Each visual is a folder: `pages/<page_id>/visuals/<visual_id>/visual.json`
- `page_id`: 20-character hex string
- `visual_id`: 16-character hex string

## Projection Structure

Every data-bound visual needs query projections. Measures use this shape:

```json
{
  "field": {
    "Measure": {
      "Expression": { "SourceRef": { "Entity": "_Measures" } },
      "Property": "Measure Name"
    }
  },
  "queryRef": "_Measures.Measure Name",
  "nativeQueryRef": "Measure Name"
}
```

Columns use `"Column"` instead of `"Measure"`.

## Query Roles by Visual Type

| visualType | Query roles |
|-----------|------------|
| cardVisual | `Data` |
| clusteredBarChart | `Category`, `Y` |
| clusteredColumnChart | `Category`, `Y` |
| tableEx | `Values` |
| slicer | `Values` |
| lineChart | `Category`, `Y` |
| scatterChart | `X`, `Y`, `Size` |

## Literal Value Suffixes

- Integer: `"5L"`
- Double: `"10D"`
- Boolean: `"true"` / `"false"`
- String: `"'Cards'"` (single-quoted inside double quotes)

## Required Schema

Always include: `"$schema": "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/fabric/item/report/definition/visualContainer/2.4.0/schema.json"`

## Styling Defaults

Use JLL Azara theme conventions unless project specifies otherwise:
- Font: Segoe UI Light
- Value font size: 26D (for cards), 10D (for labels)
- Accent bar: show true, width 1D, ThemeDataColor ColorId 0
- Padding: top 10D, bottom 10D, left 20D, right 20D

## Use Templates

Always start from an existing template in `templates/` rather than writing JSON from scratch. Fill in the `{{placeholders}}` and add projections to the empty `projections: []` array.
